title: For Sale:  Galil 5.56x45
postcontent:
New Century Arms Golani in 5.56x45. Comes with 1 -35 rd mag, metal folding stock, remove able muzzle break, threaded barrel and has a matte black finish.  These guns are far better quality than almost ALL AKs on the market. Thy have tighter tolerances and fitted better.  The Galil is kinda like an Israel AK. 

The Galil is hammer-fired and has a trigger mechanism patterned after the trigger used in the American M1 Garand.[2] 
The Galil prototypes used a stamped and riveted sheet metal steel receiver, but due to the higher operating pressures of the 5.56x45mm cartridge, this solution was discarded and the designers turned to a heavy milled forging. As a testament to its heritage, early prototypes were fabricated using Valmet Rk 62 receivers manufactured in Helsinki.[2] All exterior metal surfaces are phosphated for corrosion resistance and then coated with a black enamel (except for the barrel, gas block and front sight tower).
The weapon is fitted with a high-impact plastic handguard and pistol grip and a side-folding (folds to the right side) tubular steel skeleton stock. The rifle can be used with a sound suppressor. The weapon features a bottle opener in the front handguard and wire cutter built into the bipod. The bottle opener feature was included to prevent damage to magazines being used to open bottles, due to the large civilian reservist components of the IDF. Use of magazines to open bottles was a common source of magazine lip damage with Uzi submachine guns. Wire cutters were included to reduce the time necessary for IDF troops to cut down wire fences common to rural areas in Israel.

title: For Sale/Trade:  NWU GORETEX JACKET WITH LINER TRADE FOR GUN
postcontent:
I WANT TO TRADE MY NWU GORETEX JACKET WITH LINER FOR A GUN . 
I AM OPEN TO ANYTHING THAT IS READY TO SHOOT. BUT I AM REALLY INTERESTED IN A .22LR . MAKE CASH OFFER . THESE RETAIL FOR 250-300 NEW.

DESCRIPTION-
Navy Work Uniform (NWU) Gore-Tex® Parka
Genuine US Navy digital Gore-Tex® parka.
Parka is a soft and quiet outerwear garment constructed of strong, durable and water-resistant Gore-Tex® membrane.
Each garment is made in the USA and is windproof, breathable, and has a moisture-wicking barrier for maximum comfort and durability in even the harshest conditions.

NOTE TO MILITARY PERSONNEL: THIS GARMENT HAS NIR TECHNOLOGY AND IS APPROVED FOR MILITARY OPERATIONS

Near Infrared (NIR) Signature Management Technology is used by the U.S. Department of Defense to prevent detection by NIR Image Converters.
These photocathode devices do not detect temperatures, but rather infrared radiation variances.
NIR-compliant uniforms use a special fabric that allows servicemembers to appear at the same radiation level as the surrounding terrain, thus making them more difficult to detect. 

MORE DETAILS-

A composite layer of fabric popular for outdoor clothing and/or accessories. It is often waterproof so perfect for outwears like jackets, shoes, specialty pants (ski pants, hiking pants, etc.), and hats. It is breathable, meaning that the wearer's sweat can evaporate for comfort.

Thus, construction workers, firefighters, and other professionals who are constantly outdoors wear jackets, pants, and protective wear made from Gortex. Not to mention that Gore-Tex jackets are commonly worn by the US Navy during operation because they are constantly facing rain, heavy wind, and the harsh climate of the open seas. Cotton, linen, polyester, and sometimes, leather materials just wouldn't do.

Why wear a Gore Tex jacket?

Since World War II (and even way before that), the United States Navy had become a prevalent military force in multinational combat and had the task of protecting United States shorelines in the Pacific and Atlantic. Bases were definitely set up in other nations and regions which include Wake Islands and the Philippines. The modern Navy carried out assignments around the Atlantic Ocean, at the same time, as Navy vessels and airplanes chased Nazi submarines who were preying on Allied commercial ships. Navy bases had been strategically established in allied North Atlantic regions like Iceland for these assignments.

All of these places can be very cold, windy, and wet. Time for Gore-Tex jackets to shine.


I OWN A COUPLE OF THESE GORETEX JACKETS
